RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 4. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.

PALADIO dueled on the inside in the early going, saved ground around the turn and was caught in late stretch. REDZILLA raced in the two path around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while racing ground around the far turn and tired in the lane. THE SWEATY FOX dueled on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the second bend and faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: I AM THAT I AM raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn, dueled between horses, bumping with MAPACHE G near the eight pole and got up late. MAPACHE G raced in the three path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn, dueled down the lane, was bumped by I AM THAT I AM near the eighth pole and was outkicked from there. NOICATTARO trailed the field on the outside through the opening half mile, raced in the three path around the far turn and made no bid. NIP OF BOURBON raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, saved ground around the second turn and was empty in the stretch. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
